                        "description": "<p>Ultra High Temperature pasteurized cow milk with 3.5 % fat content (MUH Arla eG, Germany) was fermented for 72 hours with L. lactis (internal stock ID SB-261) at 30\u02daC without shaking. To harvest the whey, the fermented and then curdling milk, was centrifuged for 40 min at 7000 rpm and the supernatant was filtered sterile using 0.22 \u00b5M pore size (whey-72h). Harvested whey was then split into two parts. One was directly placed at 30\u02daC degrees without any further treatment (mock). The other part was inoculated with A. fabarum (internal stock ID SB-290) and also incubated at 30\u02daC. Samples of A. fabarum fermentation were taken after 0, 24, 48 and 72 hours (290-261-0h, 24h, 48h and 72h). The mock sample was collected after 72 hours at 30\u02daC (whey-72h-72h). Samples of milk and whey-72h were also collected for comparison. The experiment was performed in three biological replicates, R1, R2, R3.   </p>",
